direction: right

*.style.border-radius: 8
*.style.font-size: 13
*.style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
*.style.stroke: "#333333"

# --- Entry ---

args: |md
  **/test-rules-generator**

  - [repository-url]
  - optional: test type focus
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Phase 1: Repository Discovery ---

clone: |md
  **Clone & Scan**

  - git clone repo
  - find test directories
  - identify primary language
  - detect frameworks
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

detect-types: |md
  **Detect Test Types**

  - unit: *_test.go, *.spec.ts
  - mock: cypress/tests/mocked/
  - e2e: e2e/, integration/
  - contract: contract-tests/
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

infra: |md
  **Identify Infrastructure**

  - mock factories, fixtures
  - page objects
  - test utilities, helpers
  - config: jest, cypress, pytest
  - CI workflows
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- No Tests Decision ---

has-tests: |md
  **Tests
  found?**
| {
  shape: diamond
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.font-size: 12
}

no-tests: |md
  **Recommend Patterns**

  - analyze docs instead
  - suggest test frameworks
  - generate starter rules
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.stroke-dash: 5
}

# --- Phase 2: Pattern Extraction ---

collect-samples: |md
  **Collect Samples**
  LLM analysis

  - 5-10 files per test type
  - recently modified (active)
  - varying complexity
  - passing, well-structured
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#e8e8e8"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.double-border: true
}

extract-unit: |md
  **Extract Unit Patterns**
  LLM analysis

  - file structure & naming
  - describe/it conventions
  - mock/stub patterns
  - assertion styles
  - component testing (React)
  - hook testing patterns
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#e8e8e8"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.double-border: true
}

extract-mock: |md
  **Extract Mock Patterns**
  LLM analysis

  - cy.intercept patterns
  - page object methods
  - mock data factories
  - alias naming (.as)
  - validation patterns
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#e8e8e8"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.double-border: true
}

extract-e2e: |md
  **Extract E2E Patterns**
  LLM analysis

  - test-variables.yml setup
  - oc/kubectl commands
  - resource management
  - cleanup patterns
  - wait strategies
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#e8e8e8"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.double-border: true
}

extract-contract: |md
  **Extract Contract Patterns**
  LLM analysis

  - API schema validation
  - BFF startup/lifecycle
  - JSON Pointer refs
  - status code testing
  - error response patterns
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#e8e8e8"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.double-border: true
}

# --- Phase 3: Rule Generation ---

gen-standards: |md
  **Generate**
  **testing-standards.md**
  LLM generation

  - test types overview
  - when to use each type
  - general principles
  - independence & isolation
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#e8e8e8"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.double-border: true
}

gen-unit: |md
  **Generate**
  **unit-tests.md**
  LLM generation

  - framework + tools table
  - naming & location
  - patterns + examples
  - DO / DON'T checklists
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#e8e8e8"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.double-border: true
}

gen-conditional: |md
  **Generate Conditional Rules**
  LLM generation

  - mock-tests.md (if found)
  - e2e-tests.md (if found)
  - contract-tests.md (if found)
  - same template structure
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#e8e8e8"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.double-border: true
}

# --- Phase 4: Supporting Files ---

gen-support: |md
  **Generate Support Files**

  - .claude/rules/README.md
  - TEST-RULES-ANALYSIS.md
  - summary of findings
  - gap recommendations
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Phase 5: Validation ---

validate: |md
  **Validate Rules**

  - completeness check
  - accuracy vs repo code
  - file paths correct
  - framework versions match
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

test-apply: |md
  **Test Application**
  LLM generation

  - create test from rules
  - verify pattern match
  - confirm lint passes
  - adjust rules if needed
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#e8e8e8"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.double-border: true
}

# --- Output ---

output: |md
  **Output**

  .claude/rules/
  ├── testing-standards.md
  ├── unit-tests.md
  ├── mock-tests.md
  ├── e2e-tests.md
  ├── contract-tests.md
  └── README.md
  TEST-RULES-ANALYSIS.md
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#bbbbbb"
  style.stroke-width: 1
  style.font: mono
  style.font-size: 10
}

# --- Flow ---

args -> clone
clone -> detect-types
detect-types -> infra
infra -> has-tests

has-tests -> collect-samples: "yes" {
  style.stroke: "#333333"
}

has-tests -> no-tests: "no" {
  style.stroke: "#333333"
}

collect-samples -> extract-unit

extract-unit -> extract-mock: "mock tests found" {
  style.stroke: "#333333"
}

extract-unit -> extract-e2e: "e2e tests found" {
  style.stroke: "#333333"
}

extract-unit -> extract-contract: "contract tests found" {
  style.stroke: "#333333"
}

extract-unit -> gen-standards: "unit only" {
  style.stroke: "#333333"
}

extract-mock -> gen-standards
extract-e2e -> gen-standards
extract-contract -> gen-standards

gen-standards -> gen-unit
gen-unit -> gen-conditional
gen-conditional -> gen-support
gen-support -> validate
validate -> test-apply
test-apply -> output

test-apply -> validate: "rules need adjustment" {
  style.stroke-dash: 3
}

# Callout connection
gen-conditional -> output {
  style.stroke: "#bbbbbb"
  style.stroke-dash: 4
  style.stroke-width: 1
}
